        <br/><br/><strong>Radium</strong><br/>
        <strong>Radium</strong> (Ra) was discovered by Marie and Pierre Curie in 1898.
        It is the sixth member of the <strong>Uranium series</strong> and 
        all its isotopes are highly radioactive.
